                  <author>Reinach</author>, from Gaudin, no. <citedRange>207</citedRange>
               </bibl>, whence <bibl n="IGC">
                  <title n="IGC" level="m">IGC</title>
                  <citedRange>263</citedRange> and, from Reichel, <citedRange>264bis</citedRange>
               </bibl>; c. published from the <title level="m">MAMA</title> records by <bibl type="hbi" n="MAMA8">
                  <author>Cormack</author>, <title level="m">MAMA</title> 8, no. <citedRange>603</citedRange>
               </bibl>; all published by <bibl type="hbi" n="ALA">
                  <author>Roueché</author>, <title level="m">Aphrodisias in Late Antiquity</title> no. <citedRange>100</citedRange> and plate xxvi</bibl>, whence discussion by <bibl>
                  <author>Feissel</author> (<date>1991</date>), 372, n.25</bibl>, <bibl n="PHI">
                  <author>McCabe</author>
                  <title level="m">PHI Aphrodisias</title>
                  <citedRange n="257596">709</citedRange>
               </bibl>, <bibl type="hbi" n="steinepig">
                  <title level="m">Steinepigramme</title>
                  <citedRange>02/09/97</citedRange>
               </bibl>.</p>
